<comment><![CDATA[is\_active — Logical enable/disable flag for the user (orac.users).
Default 'Y'.
Allowed values: 'Y' (active), 'N' (inactive), enforced by a check constraint.
Purpose: soft-deactivate accounts without deleting related data (preferences, history remain intact).
Usage: the application should filter to active users for sign-in/assignment; historical queries should include inactive users as needed.
Change policy: toggled by admins or automated processes; does not affect foreign keys (they use user\_id).
]]></comment>
